</NavLink>
<NavLink class="nav-link" href="track">
    <span class="bi bi-search" aria-hidden="true"></span> Track
</NavLink>
```
Keep the Home link. Remove only the Counter and Weather NavLinks.

### 14. Create an EF Core migration

Run this from the server project directory (`ShipmentTracker/ShipmentTracker/`):
```bash
dotnet ef migrations add AddShipments
```
If `dotnet-ef` tool is not installed, install it first:
```bash
dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef
```

### 15. Build the solution

Run `dotnet build` from the solution root (`ShipmentTracker/`) and fix any errors.

## Important Notes
- The `.Client` project must have a project reference to nothing server-specific. The server project already references the client project.
- Do NOT add `@rendermode` to pages — it's global Auto.
- Make sure the `ShipmentTracker.Client.csproj` has `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly` package reference (it should from the template).
- The `ShipmentTracker.csproj` (server) should already reference `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite`.

